# Contributing to THE DECIPHER-er

Thanks for wanting to help out. Whether you want to fix bugs, add cool features, or improve the code, we'd love your contribution!

## How to Jump In

### 1. Fork & Clone

```bash
  git clone https://github.com/your-username/decipher-er.git
  cd decipher-er
```        

### 2. Make a Branch

Always create a new branch for your work:

```bash
git checkout -b my-feature
```

### 3. Code & Test

- Keep the Caesar cipher logic intact (offset + % 26)
- Letters get shifted, special characters stay untouched
- Test encrypt and decrypt with different shifts
- Make sure your code works with positive and negative shift values

### 4. Commit & Push

```bash
git add .
git commit -m "Add my awesome feature"
git push origin my-feature
```

### 5. Open a Pull Request

- Describe what you did clearly
- Keep each PR focused on one thing
- Reference any related issues if applicable

## A Few Tips

- Keep the code simple and readable—no fancy libraries needed
- Add comments if something is tricky (like the modulo wrapping logic)
- Test with edge cases: capital letters, numbers, special characters, and wrap-around shifts
- Don't break the existing encrypt/decrypt functionality

## What We're Looking For

- Bug fixes and performance improvements
- Better error handling and input validation
- Clearer variable names and comments
- Additional cipher methods (as separate features)
- Test cases and documentation improvements

Thanks for contributing to THE DECIPHER-er!
